{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_2hayden_ver02/data/sn83045462/00280604951/1949042001/0427.xml":{"full_text":"TERMITES!\nCausing You Trouble?\nInspection Without Obligation\nWESTERN\nExterminating Company\n1023 12th St. N.W. MS. 1520\nOffices in Principal Eastern Cities\nTRUCK BODY\nREPAIRS!\nWOOD A METAL\nTo BOYS and GIRLS with\nPIMPLY SKIN\nThey're all ravin* about It\u2014the Reslnol\nwsr to relieve externally caused pimples!\nJoin the crowd\u2014wash twld* a day with\nReslnol Boap. Then apply soothing, med\nicated Reslnol Ointment, leaving It on\nover night. Watch your skin improve!\n\u2018/a FARE\nFOR YOUR FAMILY\nMONDAYS\nTUESDAYS\nWEDNESDAYS\nWhen you purchase full fare\ntransportation for yourself, your\nwife and all children under 22\ntravel at half fare.\nPhone: STERLING 9000\nor your Travel Agent\nNORTHWEST\nL 0*1*^ AIRLINES J\n6 want a thick,\nlender, juicy steak\nso I\u2019m going to Costin\u2019s\nI feel like eating some good old\nfashioned Sauerbraten.\nso I\u2019m going to Costin\u2019s\nI want some wonderful Pried Jumbo\nShrimp\nso I\u2019m going to Costin s\n1 have a yen for a fine Wiener\nSchnitzel\u2014with buttered noodles.\nso I\u2019m going to Costin\u2019s\nI'm lust in the mood for some\ngood Fried Chicken. Golden and\nCrisp.\nso I\u2019m going to Costin s\nI'm hankering lor somt German\nPotato Pancakes.\nso I\u2019m going to Costin\u2019s\n1 could eat some real Hungarian\nGoulash\nso I\u2019m going to Costin s\nA piping hot bowl of French Onion\nSoup for me\nso I\u2019m going to Costin\u2019s\nThere Is only one place for real\nHungarian Paprika Chicken, and\nhow I love It.\nso I\u2019m going to Costin\u2019s\nT/L 9 P.M.\nArrest Based on Police\nBroadcast of $60 Theft\nContested by Defense\nIs information broadcast by the\npolice radio dispatcher in a crim\ninal case sufficiently reliable to\njustify an arrest?\nJudge Ellen K. Raedy has this\nquestion before her today, after;\nlengthy arguments in a petty lar\nceny case brought in Municipal\nCourt yesterday.\nAttorney Curtis Mitchell raised\nit in a motion to quash the arrest\nof his client, James A. Marshall, j\n21, colored, of the 200 block of\nNew York avenue N.W. He is\nunder $300 bond.\nAt the hearing, it was brought\nout that last Thursday a colored\nman entered Dave\u2019s Menswear\nShop, 705 Twelfth street N.W..;\nsnatched an armful of sportshirts\nfrom a counter and ran out a\nback door.\nMrs. Bessie Shapiro, wife of the\nowner, immediately notified police.\nPvt. Albert Mode, who investi\ngated, reported by scout car radio\nto the police dispatcher that a\n\"young colored man\u201d had stolen\n\"$60 worth\u201d of shirts from the\nstore. The dispatcher in turn\nbroadcast a lookout specifying the\n$60 value of the loot.\nTrails Marshall In Cab.\nLt. Otto Puss, cruising the vicin\nity in \"his scout car, heard the\nlookout and almost simultaneously\nsaw Marshall, carrying a card\nboard box. enter a taxicab five\nblocks from the store. Lt. Puss\ntrailed the cab to Fourth and\nRidge streets N.W., where, he said,\nhe saw Marshall jump out of the\ncab and enter a house, leaving the\nbox in the cab.\nThe lieutenant said that, while\nMarshall was in the house, he\nlooked in the box inside the cab\nand saw sports shirts. He ar\nrested Marshall when the de\nfendant came back to the cab.\nAttorney Mitchell attacked this\narrest on grounds that when Pvt.\nMode made his original report to\nthe dispatcher, he did not know\nwhat the stolen shirts were worth.\nThe lawyer emphasized Mrs.\nShapiro's testimony that she did\nnot evaluate the shirts for Pvt.\nMode\u2019s report. He also pointed\nout that the loot involved in the\ncharge against his client was val\nued only at $39.\nContends Warrant Needed.\n\"The police failed to have re\nliable cause to believe that a\nfelony had been committed,\u201d Mr.\nMitchell declared. Since the\namount Involved was leSs than\nthe $50 line set by law to separate\nthe felony of grand larceny from\nthe misdemeanor of petty larceny,\npolice had no right to make an\narrest without a warrant, he\ncharged.\n\"The radio dispatcher was\nbroadcasting unreliable informa\ntion,\u201d the attorney said. \u201cThis\nsets a bad precedent where police\ncan represent a large number of\ncrimes as felonies in their radio\nlookouts in order to facilitate\narrests.**\nAssistant United States Attorney\nRobert Scott countered by citing\npolice testimony and replaying a\ndictaphone recording of the actual\ntheft report and lookout broad\ncast over police radio at the time.\nUnder Mr. Scott\u2019s questioning,\nPvt. Mode testified that Mrs.\nShapiro informed him that shirts\nvalued at about $64 were stolen\nand that he gave that information\nto the dispatcher. The prosecutor\nargued that Mrs. Shapiro failed\nto recall this on the witness stand\nbecause she was \"nervous and ex\ncited\u201d in court.\nJudge Raedy said she will an\nnounce her decision on April 26.\nHealth Topie Announced\nDr. Thomas M. Galloway of the\nUniversity of London will discuss\n\"The British Health Plan\u201d at a\nmeeting of the District Chapter of\nthe Physicians\u2019 Forum at 8:30 p.m.\ntomorrow in the Federal Security\nBuilding, Third street and Inde\npendence avenue S.W.\nAlthough Belgium\u2019s production\nis 125 per cent of prewar, unem\nployment is above 10 per cent and\nobservers say the business outlook\nis not encouraging.\nCOSMETICS by\nDream-girl cosmetics\u2014bearing the proud iE\nname of Park Tilford\u2014at dreamy low\nprices! Never has so little money bought so\nmuch glamour! Face Powder\n\"color-keyed\" to your complexion\nLipstick in the newest\nshades...Colognes in exquisite\nfragrances...liquid perfumed\nl Deodorant! Ask for Park\njj\u00bb Tilford Cosmetics...today! .ggj\n\u25a0A^wilufl tofto MM W (|\u00abWUr\nIt\u2019s magic! It\u2019* WINX Mascara for more\nbeautiful, more magnetic eyes!\nAsk for Winx Cakt or Crummy Mtucsrs,\nEyebrow Pencil and Eye Sbndow.\nThere are no finer eye beaudfiers\nin all the world;;. yet the prices\nare as modest! Only 10# and 29#\nat all toilet-goods counters.\nWin*\nMASCARA\nPetworth Asks Bridge Railing\nBarricades to Balk Suicides\nStories of suicide took over the\nPetworth Citizens\u2019 Association\nmeeting last night, when members\ngave their opinions fit the work\nings of the suicidal mind.\nIt all started after Harvey O\nCraver, past president. Introduced\na resolution asking for railing\n\u2018\u2022barricades\u2019\u2019 on all District bridges\nto keep people from jumping off.\n\u2018\u2018It's regrettable the number of\npersons we've lost that way,\u201d he\nsaid.\nErnest Thomas said there were\nso many ways of committing sui\ncide that it wouldn't help \"even if\nwe put pets under District bridges,\nbecause a person can always jump\nout of a high window or use some\nother method that\u2019s just as good.\u201d\nDr. L. P. Hosley, psychologist,\ndisagreed with Mr. Thomas on\nwhether a thwarted suicidal will\nmake another attempt to end his\nlife. Dr. Hosley maintained it's a\nquestion of \"taking a needle that's\nstuck in a groove and starting it\nin a new path.\n\"After 60 days of confinement,\nwe\u2019ve found 60 per cent of sui\ncidals are cured.\u201d he said.\nNathan Robinson, a member of\nRescue Squad No. 2. said that the\nsquad gets from 1.200 to 2.699\nemergency calls a year and that\nmost of them involve suicide at\ntempts.\n\u201cNine of 10 times, if ire pre\nvent a suicidal death, the victim\nis most happy,\" he said.\nThe citizens agreed with Mr\nRobinson that \u201cif we can prevent\nJust on* suicide no matter what\nthe bridge safeguards cost, it will\nbe worth It.\" Mr. Craver s re\nsolution was adopted\nLast night's meeting, conducted\nby President Thomas R Manning,\nwas held in the Petworth branch\nlibrary. Georgia avenue and Ufi\nsh urs street N W,\nColombia s cost of living mdes\ncontinued to rise early this year.\nRelief\n0jr from TERMITES Nf\\\nIS^I TIMIERTOX effectively preserves wood ogemst ter-\n/\u201cSy mites, l